main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Sioux Narrows, Ontario, Canada on August 25, 1960.
interesting points: The object was tracked moving from east to west and disappeared behind trees,The observation lasted for 15 minutes,The object was reported to be at zenith,Referred to as an unknown object in subsequent investigations,The observers did not hear reports until September 13, 1960, indicating a delay in communication.
witness description: Observers reported the object but specifics on witnesses are not provided.
